  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1688642907192-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1688642907192-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1688642907192-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1688642907192-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1688642907192-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Chop your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> into smaller strips</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> chopped chicken</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until very lightly browned, then transfer to a plate and set aside</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1688642910998-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1688642910998-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1688642910998-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1688642910998-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1688642910998-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is browning, peel and roughly chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Slice your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1688642917428-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1688642917428-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1688642917428-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1688642917428-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1688642917428-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped shallot </strong>and<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> to the dish with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced green chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>,<strong> tamarind paste</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven and cook, uncovered, for an initial 25 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>curry sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-2-1688642921604-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-2-1688642921604-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-2-1688642921604-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-2-1688642921604-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-2-1688642921604-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> [600ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong></p><p>Cover tightly with <strong>tin</strong> <strong>foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>baked rice</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then shake off any excess water</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1-1688642930107-x200.jpg",
